===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In bronze inscriptions, one of the forms is a {{liushu|psc|nocap=1}} composed of {{Han compound|耂|𢏚|t1=old|c1=s|c2=p}}. It can additionally bear a decorative symbol ({{l|mul|口}}) or two ({{l|mul|口}} and {{l|mul|又}}).

The common traditional form {{lang|mul|壽}} is evolved from the composition with the two decorative symbols, with {{l|mul|又}} becoming {{l|mul|寸}}.

